# 0. Simple web stack

Whiteboard design of a one-server web infrastructure hosting the website
reachable at `www.foobar.com`.

## Diagram

```
                            ( User's computer / browser )
                                        |
                          1. "I want to visit www.foobar.com"
                                        |
                                        v
                            +-----------------------+
                            |   DNS  (foobar.com)    |
                            |  www  A  -> 8.8.8.8    |
                            +-----------------------+
                                        |
                       2. DNS answers: www.foobar.com = 8.8.8.8
                                        |
                                        v
                        3. HTTP request over TCP/IP to 8.8.8.8:80
                                        |
                                        v
        +-------------------------------------------------------------+
        |                    SERVER  (IP 8.8.8.8)                      |
        |                                                             |
        |   +-----------------+      +---------------------------+    |
        |   |   Web server    |----->|     Application server    |    |
        |   |     (Nginx)      |      | (runs the application code)|   |
        |   +-----------------+      +-------------+-------------+    |
        |          ^                               |                  |
        |          |                               v                  |
        |          |                  +---------------------------+   |
        |          |                  |    Application files       |  |
        |          |                  |    (your code base)        |  |
        |          |                  +---------------------------+   |
        |          |                               |                  |
